Diagnosis. Opercular verticil inserted on a short stalk into proximal funnel. Verticil with 5–8 spines, one very large dorsal spine made of a bulbous median part and two latero-dorsal extensions and 4–7 small outwardly curved spines positioned at the base of dorsal verticil spine, each ending in T-shaped tip, without accessory spinules. Funnel with 18–25 chitinized radii tips, base of funnel slightly chinitized. Grooves separating radii extending 1 / 3 of funnel length (
Fig. 10
).
